<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
BUSES TO BE REROUTED SUNDAY DURING MARATHON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Buses will be temporarily rerouted in Los Angeles and Hollywood Sunday during 
the Los Angeles Marathon. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County Metropolitan Transportation Authority will reroute 75 
bus lines at intervals between 7:30 a.m. and 2 p.m. in Hollywood, Downtown, 
Mid-Wilshire and Exposition Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Bus passengers are advised to plan their trips early on Sunday. For a brochure 
with information about the buses in the affected areas, call (800) 2LA-RIDE. 
</P>
<P>
 Schedule and route information is also available by calling (213) 626-4455. 
The following bus lines are some of those affected: 1, 2, 3, 4, 10, 14, 16, 18, 
20, 21, 22, 26, 27, 28, 30, 31, 33, 37, 38, 40, 42, 45, 48, 51, 53, 55, 56, 60, 
66, 67, 68, 70, 71, 76, 78, 79, 81, 83, 84, 90, 91, 92, 93, 94, 96, 97, 102. 
</P>
