<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: EL TORO 'Y' PLANS TO BE MEETINGS' TOPIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A series of meetings about the El Toro "Y's" reconstruction begins tonight in 
Laguna Hills and continues throughout the month in several South County cities. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials from the Orange County Transportation Authority and the state 
Department of Transportation will present an overview of the 2 1/2-year, 
$105-million project, intended to improve the often-congested confluence of the 
Santa Ana and and San Diego freeways.Speakers will also offer suggestions on 
using alternative routes and mass transit to avoid congestion in the 
construction area. 
</P>
<P>
 The Laguna Hills meeting tonight is at City Hall, 25201 Paseo de Alicia, Suite 
150. 
</P>
<P>
 All meetings will be from 5:30 to 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The series will continue at the following locations: 
</P>
<P>
 * Mission Viejo, March 10, Mission Viejo High School multipurpose room, 25025 
Chrisanta Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 * Irvine, March 16, Irvine Multi-Service Center, Room 1, 17200 Jamboree Road. 
</P>
<P>
 * San Juan Capistrano, March 22, Hot Spring Dance Hall, 32506 Paseo Adelanto. 
</P>
<P>
 * Laguna Niguel, March 30, Design Center South, 23811 Aliso Creek Road. 
RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</TEXT>
