<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; CITY SOROPTIMISTS TO HOLD LUNCH BENEFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Soroptimist International of Buena Park will hold its eighth annual community 
benefit luncheon Wednesday, with proceeds going to local nonprofit groups. 
</P>
<P>
 The money raised will be spent to buy shoes for needy children, give food, 
clothing and shelter to low-income families and the homeless, and provide 
activities for underprivileged youth. 
</P>
<P>
 Among local groups receiving funds will be the Boys & Girls Club of Buena 
Park, the Speech and Language Development Center, Buena Park Coordinating 
Council and the DARE Program. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited and a $5 donation is requested for the luncheon, which 
will be served continuously from 11:45 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. Tickets are available 
at the door at the Buena Park Community Recreation Center, 8150 Knott Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Patsy Marshall, publicity chairwoman, said the organization holds several 
fund-raisers during the year including the Silverado Ball, which is the kickoff 
to the city's fall Silverado Days, and an annual garage sale in April. 
</P>
<P>
 Marshall said the group raises about $5,000 a year. 
</P>
<P>
 Luncheon tickets are also available at the Buena Park Chamber of Commerce 
office, 6280 Manchester Blvd., Suite 102, or by calling (714) 821-3620. 
</P>
</TEXT>
