<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEVERAL INJURED WHEN PURSUIT ENDS IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several people were injured Tuesday when a vehicle being chased by Cypress 
police ran a red light and crashed into two other vehicles, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress police were pursuing the vehicle when the accident occurred at 9:30 
p.m. at the intersection of Knott and Orange avenues, according to Sgt. Richard 
Zschoche of the Anaheim police. 
</P>
<P>
 Emergency personnel took at least two people to area hospitals, dispatchers 
said. 
</P>
