<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: SUDDENLY, LAKE PIRU A BASS HAVEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lake Piru is not reputed to be a bass fishery like nearby Lake Casitas and 
Castaic Lake, but in the past week anglers at the Ventura County reservoir did 
much to boost its reputation as such. 
</P>
<P>
 Aron Masters of Chatsworth, fishing with plastic worms throughout the lake, 
caught and released 60 bass, including two 5-pounders. Dick Denlinger of 
Moorpark, meanwhile, hauled in a 13 1/2-pounder that attacked his Rapala lure. 
Garrett Godfrey of Fillmore, was fishing for trout with Power Bait in a marina 
when a 9-pounder struck. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've been here 15 years and I've never seen anything like it," marina manager 
Art Caldara said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
