<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Professional Soccer League announced expansion into two cities 
and a new ownership group and team in Toronto Tuesday, bringing APSL membership 
for the upcoming season to eight. 
</P>
<P>
 Seattle (Sounders) and Houston (Force) will be the new league cities. The 
Toronto Rockets will replace the defunct Toronto Blizzard. 
</P>
