<P>
DIVISION II GIRLS' SOCCER; TOP-SEEDED TEAM KNOCKS OUT CANYON, 2-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon took a one-goal lead into the second half, but couldn't hang on and 
fell, 2-1, to visiting Torrance Bishop Montgomery in a Southern Section 
Division II girls' soccer semifinal Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Comanches (17-6-3), who reached the Division II final last season, entered 
the game as heavy underdogs to the top-seeded Knights (20-2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Midway through the first half, Canyon struck first, when Kim Nelson passed to 
Kerry Anderson leading a three-on-none break. Anderson pushed the ball to the 
left of goalkeeper Celeste Adams for the early advantage. 
</P>
<P>
 The lead held until the Knights scored with about 20 minutes left to play.  
</P>
<P>
 Canyon goalkeeper Robin Schmidt came out of the box trying to cut off the 
angle on a Bishop Montgomery corner kick. The ball slid past her in front of 
the goal and right to Bishop Montgomery's Bridgett Arnett, who kicked it in. 
The referee ruled that the ball cleared the goal line just before two Canyon 
defenders cleared it. 
</P>
<P>
 Less than two minutes later, Schmidt left the box again and Michelle Kallas 
kicked it into the upper left corner. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was (Schmidt's) call to go out and try to mess up the play," Canyon Coach 
John Williams said. "Their girl had no angle at all. I thought the first goal 
was cleared, but the referee had a much better angle than I did." 
</P>
<P>
 Adams snuffed out Canyon's chances late in the second half, recording three of 
her seven saves in the last 10 minutes. Schmidt had eight saves for Canyon. JON 
CLIFFORD 
</P>
