<TEXT>
<P>
 Esperanza and Buena played 120 minutes of scoreless soccer before the Aztecs 
finally won the game on the last shot of the shootout in a Southern Section 
Division II girls' soccer game Tuesday at Buena. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza's Kim Gallo kicked the ball past goalkeeper Stacy Hebert to give the 
Aztecs the shootout, 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Unseeded Esperanza (20-5-4) advanced to the title game against top-seeded 
Bishop Montgomery at 2 p.m. Saturday at Cerritos Gahr High. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is not the way I planned it to happen," Esperanza Coach Phyllis 
Scarborough said. "Nobody likes to go the finals on a shootout, but those are 
the rules." 
</P>
<P>
 Bishop Montgomery (20-2-2) reached the final with a 2-1 victory over Canyon 
Tuesday. 
</P>
