</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ZANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Esperanza needed overtime, sudden death and then a shootout Tuesday to earn a 
chance to defend its Southern Section Division II boys' soccer title. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza and top-seeded Santa Barbara were tied, 1-1, after regulation and 
overtime, but the Aztecs won the shootout, 3-2.Esperanza (18-5-5) will play 
Mater Dei (23-2-4) for the title at 8 p.m. Saturday at Cerritos Gahr High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza led the shootout, 3-2, when Santa Barbara's Garrett Cole set up for 
the final kick, but Aztec goalie Jason Fiske drove to his right to knock away 
the ball. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara (26-2-2) took a 1-0 lead in the first half on a goal by Carlos 
Moralas. Esperanza came back to tie it about 17 minutes into the first half 
when Mark Alleman scored his 19th goal of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara appeared to have scored three minutes later, but the official 
waved off the goal saying it was supposed to be an indirect kick, not a free 
kick. JOHN ZANT 
</P>
