<P>
PREP NOTES: NOFFSINGER TO PLAY SOFTBALL AT MICHIGAN STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stefanie Noffsinger, an All-Southern Section pitcher for Huntington Beach 
High, has orally committed to play softball at Michigan State. 
</P>
<P>
 Noffsinger, who also has been named to the All-Sunset League team three times, 
has a career earned-run average of 0.61.She has also lettered in volleyball, 
basketball, cross-country and field hockey. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra softball Coach Sue Briquelet has been named coach of the year for 
1994 by the California Coaches Assn., and will receive her award at a Walnut 
Creek CCA conference March 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Briquelet, a math teacher, has compiled a 48-8 record in three years at La 
Habra; the Highlanders reached the Southern Section semifinals each season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Because of Santa Margarita's participation in a Southern Section boys' 
basketball championship game at 11:15 a.m. Saturday at Anaheim Arena, the Walk 
for Darren scheduled for that morning has been moved up an hour to 8-11. 
</P>
<P>
 Walkers will earn money to help pay for a special van for Darren Wedertz, a 
former Santa Margarita football player who was injured in a game and also has 
leukemia. 
</P>
