<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE BASEBALL; BOTTOM OF ORDER COMES UP BIG FOR GOLDEN WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The bottom four hitters in Golden West's lineup combined for eight hits and 
drove in eight runs as the Rustlers beat Orange Coast, 9-5, in an Orange Empire 
Conference baseball game Tuesday at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Fann had three hits and drove in a run.Erin Winemiller had two hits, 
including a triple, and drove in three runs. Mitch Charles had a triple and 
drove in three runs and Jake Smith added two hits, including a double and an 
RBI. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West (7-6, 1-1 in conference) scored three runs in the fifth to take a 
6-3 lead, then added three in the seventh to go ahead, 9-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Yakura had a single and a triple and Scorr MacDermott had two hits and 
an RBI for Orange Coast (3-7, 0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 4, Fullerton 0 -- Jeff Biron pitched a six-hitter, striking out 
seven, and Wade Jackson had three hits, including a triple, for Saddleback 
(6-5, 1-1). David Biddinger had a single and drove in two runs for Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 7, Cypress 6 (10 innings) -- Visiting Cypress (13-4) lost its 
conference opener. Riverside is 12-2, 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In a nonconference game: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 9, San Diego City 1 -- Matt Kastelic, Joe Fraser and Darren 
Troilo had doubles and Brian Carlson had a triple for visiting Rancho Santiago 
(13-2). The Dons scored five runs in the eighth to go ahead, 9-1. 
</P>
