<P>
 A tough team to figure, last year and this season. The Spartans were 
runners-up in the Santa Ana Elks tournament but missed the playoffs by one game 
last season. They have a good nucleus back. Parker and Brady give them two 
solid starters. Brady was a second-team Times Orange County selection as a 
kicker in football. They had better pitch well because they are unlikely to get 
much support. The Spartans need players to develop as hitters, something Wilson 
said hasn't happened yet. The left side of the infield is strong with McMahon, 
the starting quarterback last fall, and Case, who was a first-team all-league 
selection. Halbert was honorable mention all-league, so the Spartans are set at 
catcher. Then come the questions. The outfield spots are up for grabs, except 
for D'Amato. Second base is anyone's guess. There are several good, but 
inexperienced, pitchers if Brady or Parker falter. The best of them is Hansen, 
who worked out of the bullpen last season. 
