should be in the running again this year, as they have two experienced 
pitchers. Hanson and May have been on the varsity since they were sophomores. 
Hanson was 6-2 and May 4-5 last season. "We're going to count heavily on those 
two," Mott said. "Our pitching will be strong. It will all depend on how we do 
some of the little things." Such as hit. Gross led the team last season, 
batting better than .400, but most of the young batters will need time to 
develop. Only four seniors were on the varsity last season. "I don't think 
hitting will be a problem," Mott said. "But we're going to have to do things 
like bunt and hit and run. I told our kids, if we're in the game going into the 
seventh inning, we have a chance because of our pitching." 
</P>
</TEXT>
