<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; NASTER SHARP AS MOORPARK WINS OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Naster (3-0) scattered six hits and struck out seven to lead Moorpark 
College to a 5-2 victory over Santa Barbara in a Western State Conference 
baseball opener Tuesday at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Kent Cote had three hits and Kevin Nykoluk added a double and a home run for 
Moorpark (4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 4, Santa Monica 1 -- Brian Warner broke a tie in the eighth inning 
with a two-run triple in a WSC opener at Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 Cuesta 7, Oxnard 2 -- Adam Basua, Matt Anderson and Armando Macial each had 
two hits for the Condors (3-8), who came up short in a WSC opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce 3, Canyons 1 -- Run-scoring singles in the sixth inning by Cesar 
Martinez and Brian Sturges broke a 1-1 tie in a WSC opener at Canyons.  
