<P>
 Bakersfield 9, Valley 1 -- David Stevenson went three for three and has 
reached base in nine consecutive at-bats, but the Monarchs (2-8-1) lost a WSC 
opener at Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 13, Cal Lutheran 3 -- Mark Vail drove in three runs with a triple 
and a double to lead the Mustangs (6-6-2) in a nonconference game at Newhall. 
Chris Fick homered for the Kingsmen. 
</P>
<P>
 Citrus 16, Antelope Valley 4 -- Citrus had 16 hits in a Foothill Conference 
opener at Glendora. SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 13-8, La Verne 3-5 -- The Regals (4-2, 4-0) had 33 hits in a 
Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference doubleheader. In the 
opener, Laree Reynolds hit two home runs and a double, and drove in seven runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 3, Ventura 0 -- Heather Meyer fired a one-hitter and struck 
out nine for Antelope Valley in a nonconference game. MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 CS Northridge d. UC Irvine, 15-13, 15-12, 15-10 -- Oliver Heitmann and Jason 
Hughes each had 22 kills for visiting Northridge in the Mountain Pacific Sports 
Federation match. Collin Smith added 15 kills for the Matadors, who play host 
to No. 1-ranked and defending NCAA champion UCLA on Thursday night. 
</P>
