<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michelle Nuesca 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: La Reina 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Soccer 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Nuesca scored a team-high 26 goals as the Regents (22-2) 
reached the Division IV semifinals Tuesday before losing to Chadwick, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Nuesca, a midfielder, scored three goals in La Reina's two 
playoff victories, and in the process became the school's all-time leading 
scorer.The four-year starter scored both goals in the Regents' 2-0 quarterfinal 
victory over Marlborough last Thursday. That gave her 86 in her career and 
broke the record of 84 set last season by Jaimie Armstrong. An unselfish 
player, Nuesca also has 64 assists, a school record. "She's excellent," Coach 
Joe Laraneta said. "She plays side to side, goal to goal and plays as hard 
defensively as she does offensively." 
</P>
