<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: NEWPORT CORP. LOSES $3.7 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Corp., an Irvine manufacturer of precision equipment for the 
development of laser and optics technology, posted a net loss of $3.7 million, 
or 53 cents a share, for 1993, which included restructuring and other special 
charges totaling $5.1 million.Sales were $84.1 million. Because the company 
changed its fiscal year end from July 31 to Dec. 31 as of Jan. 1, comparable 
results are not available for prior-year periods. The fourth-quarter net loss 
was $4.7 million, or 67 cents a share, on sales of $19.9 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
