<TEXT>
<P>
 Viacom Cable TV Unit Eliminates 43 Jobs: Viacom Inc.'s cable TV systems 
division said it has eliminated 43 positions, most of them at its Pleasanton, 
Calif., headquarters. A company official said the cuts represent about 2% of 
the work force and were made necessary by recent federal regulations rolling 
back cable rates. He said about 15 of the displaced employees will be offered 
other positions. 
