<TEXT>
<P>
 Times Mirror Co. to Acquire Software Maker: The parent company of the Los 
Angeles Times said it will purchase Allen Communication Inc. The price was not 
disclosed, but the company indicated it was for less than $10 million.Salt Lake 
City-based Allen makes multimedia and software products, and is best known for 
its Quest word-processing software designed for DOS operating systems. Times 
Mirror said its three professional training companies -- Learning 
International, Zenger-Miller and Kaset International -- will use Allen software 
to enhance their products. Times Mirror's Jeppeson Sanderson, a publisher of 
flight information and aviation training materials, will also develop training 
programs using the technology. 
