<TEXT>
<P>
 Video Game Makers Will Use Movie-Type Ratings: The U.S. video game industry 
has tentatively decided that an anonymous panel of parents, psychologists and 
educators will rate computer games according to the violence and sex they 
contain, industry executives said.The panel would be appointed by a trade 
association that the $6-billion-a-year industry plans to set up. During the 
pre-Christmas rush of game releases, it would have perhaps 25 members. The 
ratings system resembles very closely one that the Motion Picture Assn. of 
America has used to categorize films for 25 years. 
</P>
