</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 2, 1994, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
66 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co. paid Stanley Gault, its chairman and chief 
executive officer, a bonus of more than $1 million in 1993, the company's proxy 
statement shows. Goodyear also boosted Gault's salary 6.9% to $935,000, from 
$875,000 in 1992. . . . Defense contractor Loral Corp. said it has completed 
the previously announced acquisition of IBM Federal Systems for $1.5 billion in 
cash. 
</P>
