<P>
 Ford Strike in Mexico Ends: The auto maker's Mexico unit signed a new contract 
with workers, ending a two-week strike at Ford's Chihuahua plant.Ford Motor Co. 
workers walked off their jobs at the plant in northern Mexico on Feb. 9 after 
union leaders and company representatives failed to reach agreement. They 
returned to work after accepting the company's latest wage increase proposal. 
Under the new contract, the workers will receive a 5% wage increase and a 3% 
increase in productivity bonuses. Ford also agreed to raise their compensation 
2% through indirect benefits, such as food coupons and bonuses. The Chihuahua 
plant, which employs 618 people, is designed to produce Ford's new, 
four-cylinder "Z" engine. 
