<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOXER SUFFERS SERIOUS INJURY AT THE FORUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Boxer Miguel Mercedes was in serious condition late Tuesday night after a vein 
burst in his skull after a bout at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Mercedes was taken to Westside Hospital and later moved to Cedars Sinai, where 
a neurosurgeon was scheduled to meet with ringside physician Robert Karns and 
decide if surgery was needed immediately.Karns said that Mercedes did have 
swelling but that he was conscious. 
</P>
<P>
 After referee Jim Jen Kin stopped the fight at 45 seconds of the 10th and 
final round, with Mercedes trapped against the ropes by super-flyweight Cecilio 
Espino, Mercedes walked back to his corner and then lost consciousness. 
</P>
<P>
 He quickly regained his senses, and was speaking to attendants about 10 
minutes after the fight. 
</P>
<P>
 On May 28, 1989, in Mexico, Hector Ruiz died of head injuries suffered in a 
fight against Espino. 
</P>
