</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NCAA REJECTS CLU'S APPEAL TO MOVE PLAYOFF SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The NCAA Division III basketball playoff committee has turned down Cal 
Lutheran's appeal to change the site for Saturday night's second-round game 
between the Kingsmen and the winner of Thursday night's Pomona-Pitzer-UC San 
Diego contest. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran Coach Mike Dunlap proposed that the game be played at Occidental 
College at 7:30 p.m. after the Division III playoff committee announced that 
the Kingsmen (24-2) would have to play at the home court of the winner of 
Thursday night's game. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran, top-seeded team in the West region, was expecting to play host 
to a second-round game after a first-round bye, but the size of its court 
(smaller than the standard 94 x 50 feet) and the limited seating capacity (800) 
at its gymnasium do not meet the NCAA's specifications for a playoff site. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark College was available, but it could be guaranteed only for an 
afternoon game because the Raiders could be playing host to a Southern 
California regional final that night if the Raiders defeat Southwestern 
tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 The Division III playoff committee believed it was unfair for the 
Pomona-Pitzer-UC San Diego winner to have to play Saturday afternoon after 
playing Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's hard to get the NCAA to change anything," Dunlap said. "Now we just need 
to get off of this and get on to preparing for Saturday night." JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</TEXT>
