<TEXT>
<P>
 Brazil Tries a 12th Anti-Inflation Index: The government introduced the real 
value unit, or URV, an index designed to curb runaway inflation.The URV, pegged 
to the U.S. dollar, will be used to calculate salaries and, eventually, all 
financial transactions. The index replaces 11 others that, over the years, have 
been used to determine everything from interest rates to grocery prices. The 
new one is supposed to reduce inflation, now running at more than 40% a month, 
to a single-digit figure. Last year, inflation reached an annual rate of 
2,567%. 
</P>
