AMERICAN SHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Susan Christian / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Uncle Sam says thanks to Melrose Industries for buying American. 
</P>
<P>
 The small Huntington Beach company leases U.S. merchant ships to export its 
product: bulk paper used to make toilet and facial tissue.On Thursday, the U.S. 
Department of Transportation's Maritime Administration will award the paper 
broker a certificate of appreciation during a ceremony on the Queen Mary in 
Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 "We give preference to American-flagged vessels," said David Rose, president 
of Melrose Industries. "Supporting the American-flagged fleet is very important 
to the overall security of the country." 
</P>
<P>
 In a national emergency, such as the Gulf War three years ago, the government 
can press American-flagged ships into service. 
</P>
